ERASE [-C] device [name]The disk directory is reinitialized (as a ProDOS volume if not under GS/OS)Parameters:     -C         Do not prompt before destroying the current contents of the                disk.  GS/OS itself always prompts, so this option becomes                the default when running under GS/OS.     device     Device name (e.g. .D1) of the device to format.  A volume                name may be used if the disk has already been formatted.     name       Name to assign to the new disk.  If you do not specify a                name, the current volume name of the disk is used, if possible.                Copyright by Peter Watson, February 1989.